Package org.team639.robot.commands.cube

Commands pertaining to the cube acquisition

See: Description

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AngleShootCube  
    CloseAcquisition
    Tells the acquisition to close and then immediately ends.
    CloseAndIntake
    Closes and intakes, assuming there is a cube within reach.
    CloseOnCubeAtBack
    Starts intaking a cube once the back sensor is triggered.
    CloseOnCubeAtFront
    Starts intaking a cube once the front sensor is triggered.
    EjectCube
    Ejects a held cube.
    FloatAcquisition
    A command that tells the acquisition to float and then immediately finishes.
    IntakeCube
    Runs the acquisition motors inwards.
    LaunchCube
    Launches a cube
    LowerAcquisition
    A command that tells the acquisition to lower and then immediately finishes.
    MonitorCube
    A command that tries to hold on to a cube if it is knocked loose.
    OpenAcquisition
    A command that tells the acquisition to open and then immediately finishes.
    PositionCube
    A command that correctly positions a cube within the acquisition.
    RaiseAcquisition
    A command that tells the acquisition to raise and then immediately finishes.
    SetAcquisitionSpinning
    Sets the acquisition motors spinning at a given speed.
    SetShouldHaveCube
    Tells the cube acquisition system whether it should currently have a cube.
    WaitForBackAndClosedSensors
    A command that waits for both the back sensor and arms closed sensor of the acquisition to return true.
    WaitForCubeAtBack
    A command that waits for a cube to be detected in the acquisition.
    WaitForCubeAtFront
    A command that waits for the front acquisition sensor to be triggered.
